Bob placed three regular pentagons together at a vertex, thinking he might be able to form a tessellation. However, they left a gap. What is the number of degrees in the measure indicated? [asy]size(100);
path A = dir(0) -- dir(72) -- dir (144) -- dir(216) -- dir (288) -- cycle;
path B = reflect ( dir(72), dir(144)) * A;
path C = reflect( dir(72), dir(0))* A;
draw(rotate(18) *A);
draw(rotate(18) *B);
draw(rotate(18) *C);
label("?", (0,1.5), N);
[/asy]

Line $l$ is a straight line. What is the value of $x$ in the diagram? [asy]
size(150); defaultpen(linewidth(0.8)); import geometry;
draw(origin--(10,0),Arrows);
pair X = (5,0) + 5*dir(80);
draw((5,0)--X,EndArrow);
label("$x$",(5.4,0),NE);
label("$x+20^\circ$",(5,0),NW);
label("$l$",(0,0),NW);
[/asy]

Points $A,$ $B,$ and $C$ are placed on a circle centered at $O$ as in the following diagram: [asy]
pair pA, pB, pC, pO;
pO = (0, 0);
pA = pO + dir(-40);
pB = pO + dir(32);
pC = pO + dir(176);
draw(pA--pO--pB--pC--pA);
label("$O$", pO, 2 * E);
label("$A$", pA, SE);
